1
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:12,269
<i>I don't know whether you've ever
seen a map of a person's mind.</i>

2
00:01:13,673 --> 00:01:17,165
<i>Doctors sometimes draw maps
of other parts of you,</i>

3
00:01:17,243 --> 00:01:21,009
<i>and your own map can become
intensely interesting,</i>

4
00:01:21,081 --> 00:01:24,949
<i>but catch them trying to draw
a map of a child's mind,</i>

5
00:01:25,085 --> 00:01:29,954
<i>which is not only confused,
but keeps going round all the time.</i>

6
00:01:31,825 --> 00:01:36,592
<i>There are zigzag lines on it,
just like your temperature on a card,</i>

7
00:01:37,530 --> 00:01:40,897
<i>and these are probably roads
in the island,</i>

8
00:01:41,835 --> 00:01:46,033
<i>for the Neverland is always
more or less an island.</i>

9
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:50,666
You idiot! What the hell
do you think you're doing?

10
00:01:50,743 --> 00:01:52,210
No, it's okay. It's fine.

11
00:01:52,278 --> 00:01:54,508
Get off the beach, you stupid moron!

12
00:01:54,614 --> 00:01:56,081
What's your problem?

13
00:01:56,149 --> 00:01:57,912
What do you think you're doing,
you clown?

14
00:01:58,051 --> 00:02:00,144
Take it easy. Relax.

15
00:02:01,287 --> 00:02:04,745
You're insane! Get that child off there!

16
00:02:06,726 --> 00:02:09,320
- Right on!
- Yeah!

17
00:02:17,170 --> 00:02:21,266
- Do you want to get wet?
- No! I don't want to!

18
00:02:21,374 --> 00:02:23,137
You do. You love it.

19
00:02:44,531 --> 00:02:47,523
Get off the windscreen,
you horrible little bug.

20
00:03:45,024 --> 00:03:47,117
<i>I wouldn't be the first to say
that life is a journey</i>

21
00:03:47,193 --> 00:03:49,957
<i>that must be traveled
no matter how bad the road.</i>

22
00:03:51,264 --> 00:03:55,132
<i>When Artie's mother was alive,
the place didn't look like this.</i>

23
00:03:55,835 --> 00:03:58,599
<i>The house was just
so much more welcoming.</i>

24
00:03:59,005 --> 00:04:00,996
<i>Everywhere you turned,
Katy was there,</i>

25
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:03,702
<i>in the smell of freshly-picked
rosemary in the kitchen,</i>

26
00:04:05,044 --> 00:04:08,571
<i>the tomatoes from the garden,
the vase of flowers in the window.</i>

27
00:04:10,316 --> 00:04:13,615
<i>We miss that now. We do miss that.</i>

28
00:04:14,988 --> 00:04:17,786
Stop washing your face?
Are you crazy?

29
00:04:17,890 --> 00:04:20,518
<i>"...for Neverland
is always more or less an island,</i>

30
00:04:20,593 --> 00:04:23,619
"with astonishing splashes of color
here and there,

31
00:04:23,730 --> 00:04:27,131
"and coral reefs
and rakish-looking craft in the offing."

32
00:04:27,132 --> 00:04:28,695
Do you want to try reading
some of that yourself?

33
00:04:28,768 --> 00:04:30,167
- Where, Mum?
- Here.

34
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:35,131
"You could say of them

35
00:04:35,208 --> 00:04:40,202
"that they have each other's noises..."
Noise...

36
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:44,614
- Nose.
- "...nose and so forth."

37
00:04:48,588 --> 00:04:51,352
- That looks good, Mum.
- I hope I've made enough.

38
00:04:52,692 --> 00:04:56,594
- Katy, he's here.
- Look, Artie, it's your long-lost father.

39
00:04:56,663 --> 00:04:57,755
Daddy!

40
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,127
- Hello, stranger.
- Hey, you.

41
00:05:04,437 --> 00:05:07,964
- Daddy!
- Hey, cheeky bum. Here's your pressie.

42
00:05:08,041 --> 00:05:10,100
- Welcome home, mate.
- Digby.

43
00:05:10,101 --> 00:05:12,375
- Good copy.
- You like the piece on Nadal?

44
00:05:12,445 --> 00:05:14,970
- How was the old country?
- Same old Wimbledon.

45
00:05:15,048 --> 00:05:17,915
Strawberries with lashings
of English rain.

46
00:05:18,051 --> 00:05:21,111
- Hi.
- Good to see you.

47
00:05:21,112 --> 00:05:22,248
- Hiya, Barbara.
- Hi.

48
00:05:22,355 --> 00:05:24,755
You shouldn't have gone
to all this trouble just for me.

49
00:05:24,824 --> 00:05:26,689
As if.

50
00:05:26,759 --> 00:05:29,489
- That got my name on it, Tom?
- Branded it myself.

51
00:05:29,562 --> 00:05:32,030
All right, kids, let's have
an Olympic race. Line up here.

52
00:05:32,131 --> 00:05:34,224
On your markies,
get your car keys. Go!

53
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:36,131
- Go!
- Come back for sunscreen

54
00:05:36,132 --> 00:05:37,993
...when you're done.
- Go, Eddie!

55
00:05:38,071 --> 00:05:40,835
<i>And so we lived
happily ever after.</i>

56
00:05:40,907 --> 00:05:43,137
- Come on, now.
- Gold, silver...

57
00:05:43,138 --> 00:05:45,409
<i>Now, you know that's not true,
don't you?</i>

58
00:05:45,478 --> 00:05:47,070
Is this okay?

59
00:05:48,081 --> 00:05:51,073
- You look great.
- But?

60
00:05:51,150 --> 00:05:53,880
- But what?
- There was a "but" in your voice.

61
00:05:53,986 --> 00:05:56,477
- You don't like it?
- I do. It's just...

62
00:05:57,023 --> 00:05:58,888
Just what?

63
00:05:58,958 --> 00:06:00,892
Well, it's a little black number.
What can I say?

64
00:06:00,993 --> 00:06:02,460
What does that mean?

65
00:06:02,528 --> 00:06:04,689
- I like this one.
- For God's sake.

66
00:06:04,764 --> 00:06:06,129
Are you saying
you want me to change?

67
00:06:06,130 --> 00:06:08,762
- No.
- Then tell me you like this dress.

68
00:06:08,835 --> 00:06:11,827
All right. I'll tell you I love the dress,
but only on the strict understanding

69
00:06:11,904 --> 00:06:14,429
that you know
I'm not telling the truth, okay?

70
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:16,835
Just tell me what you think of the dress.

71
00:06:16,909 --> 00:06:20,675
I love that dress. That dress is fantastic.

72
00:06:21,647 --> 00:06:24,081
Thank you. At last.

73
00:06:25,885 --> 00:06:28,513
It was very good. Very...

74
00:06:28,654 --> 00:06:29,746
Just picture it.

75
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:32,187
- I just find it does capture it...
- Sounds great.

76
00:06:33,126 --> 00:06:35,060
But, you know,
I think it would be fantastic...

77
00:06:35,128 --> 00:06:37,562
Excuse me. Sorry, sorry. Hi.

78
00:06:37,630 --> 00:06:40,929
Hi. How are you? How are you?
We're just going to grab some air.

79
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,934
Thank you. Nice to meet you.

80
00:06:43,002 --> 00:06:44,663
- What was that?
- Oh, my God.

81
00:06:44,771 --> 00:06:47,968
You just saved me
from the most boring man ever.

82
00:06:58,251 --> 00:07:00,446
My God, you're beautiful.

83
00:07:02,488 --> 00:07:04,115
In a slightly spooky kind of way.

84
00:07:06,359 --> 00:07:07,553
Katy?

85
00:07:17,403 --> 00:07:19,633
These will be safer with you.

86
00:07:46,933 --> 00:07:48,332
I'm so sorry.

87
00:07:50,703 --> 00:07:52,193
Don't be silly.

88
00:07:57,844 --> 00:08:00,972
- She'll be fine. I know she'll be fine.
- How do you know?

89
00:08:01,047 --> 00:08:02,844
Well, I know
she won't let this defeat her.

90
00:08:02,915 --> 00:08:05,645
- What, you know she's immortal?
- No, I'm just saying...

91
00:08:05,751 --> 00:08:07,912
Digby, she's sicker than shit.

92
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:10,679
The cancer has rooted in her bowel

93
00:08:10,756 --> 00:08:12,587
and grown through her body
like Russian vine.

94
00:08:12,692 --> 00:08:15,388
She's got two tumors in her intestine,
three in her liver,

95
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:16,962
which means
it's probably spread to her lungs.

96
00:08:17,029 --> 00:08:19,793
You don't have a clue
what you're talking about.

97
00:08:23,803 --> 00:08:25,236
I'm so sorry.

98
00:09:02,675 --> 00:09:04,973
It's okay, sweetheart.
Gently.

99
00:09:26,198 --> 00:09:27,563
Hey.

100
00:09:32,572 --> 00:09:35,200
You know how Mummy's been getting
more and more tired

101
00:09:35,274 --> 00:09:37,265
because she's been so ill?

102
00:09:40,446 --> 00:09:43,347
We think that soon, she's going to go
into a very deep sleep.

103
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:52,054
A sleep so deep that we don't think
she's ever going to wake up again.

104
00:09:57,163 --> 00:09:58,994
We think she's going to die.

105
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:02,829
When?

106
00:10:04,070 --> 00:10:05,332
Soon.

107
00:10:07,006 --> 00:10:09,133
Will Mummy die by dinner time?

108
00:10:11,477 --> 00:10:13,035
I don't know.

109
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:17,243
Will she die by bedtime?

110
00:10:19,719 --> 00:10:23,382
I don't know, sweetheart.
None of us knows.

111
00:10:24,490 --> 00:10:25,889
Okay.

112
00:10:48,047 --> 00:10:49,605
Katy?

113
00:10:57,423 --> 00:10:58,754
Katy?

114
00:10:59,692 --> 00:11:03,958
I'm making Artie's lunch.
The way he likes it.

115
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:06,995
It's the middle of the night.

116
00:11:10,169 --> 00:11:11,431
What?

117
00:11:12,071 --> 00:11:16,132
Artie's in bed, sweetheart. He's asleep.

118
00:11:20,346 --> 00:11:21,370
Oh, no.

119
00:11:23,115 --> 00:11:24,104
It's okay.

120
00:12:04,123 --> 00:12:05,886
Did Mummy die last night?

121
00:12:13,232 --> 00:12:14,631
Artie...

122
00:12:16,535 --> 00:12:18,969
See? See? I told you. I told you.

123
00:12:19,572 --> 00:12:20,937
What did you tell me?

124
00:12:21,006 --> 00:12:23,304
I told you Mummy would die last night.

125
00:12:30,316 --> 00:12:34,480
Oh, my baby. My baby.

126
00:12:36,922 --> 00:12:39,857
My baby. My baby.

127
00:13:30,676 --> 00:13:33,008
<i>If you want to
leave a message for Felicity or Harry,</i>

128
00:13:33,078 --> 00:13:34,978
<i>please speak after the tone.</i>

129
00:13:35,548 --> 00:13:38,415
Flick, it's Joe.
I guess it's about lunchtime there.

130
00:13:38,517 --> 00:13:40,041
Listen, could you call me
as soon as you get the...

131
00:13:40,152 --> 00:13:41,346
<i>Dad?</i>

132
00:13:42,154 --> 00:13:44,349
<i>- Harry?
- Hi.</i>

133
00:13:45,991 --> 00:13:48,323
I thought you'd be away at school.

134
00:13:49,728 --> 00:13:53,562
<i>Are you okay?
What is it you wanted to tell Mum?</i>

135
00:13:56,402 --> 00:13:59,166
Katy passed away
in the early hours of this morning.

136
00:14:04,877 --> 00:14:06,367
<i>I'm so sorry.</i>

137
00:14:09,748 --> 00:14:11,716
Could you tell your mother for me?

138
00:14:11,784 --> 00:14:13,217
<i>Of course.</i>

139
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:21,516
Harry, can I call you back?

140
00:14:24,597 --> 00:14:27,122
<i>- Are you going to be okay?
- Yeah, of course I am.</i>

141
00:14:30,436 --> 00:14:31,926
I love you.

142
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:36,035
<i>I love you, too. I miss you, Daddy.</i>

143
00:15:13,612 --> 00:15:16,877
- Daddy?
- Yes, sweetheart?

144
00:15:16,982 --> 00:15:18,609
I want to die.

145
00:15:20,386 --> 00:15:21,910
Do you?

146
00:15:23,956 --> 00:15:26,789
- Why?
- So I can be with Mummy.

147
00:15:32,064 --> 00:15:36,091
Don't worry, Daddy.
I'll stay down here with you for now.

148
00:15:38,003 --> 00:15:39,368
Thanks.

149
00:15:41,173 --> 00:15:44,165
- Take care.
- I'll see you soon, all right?

150
00:15:49,682 --> 00:15:52,116
Come on, Artie,
let's get you into your jammies.

151
00:15:53,152 --> 00:15:56,053
- Artie...
- Bea, leave him alone.

152
00:15:56,121 --> 00:15:58,055
Let him run around if he wants.

153
00:15:59,291 --> 00:16:01,122
Do you really need that?

154
00:16:02,027 --> 00:16:04,791
Well, at least you should try
and eat something.

155
00:16:04,863 --> 00:16:06,330
I can't do this.

156
00:16:40,165 --> 00:16:41,689
Oh, God.

157
00:18:19,731 --> 00:18:21,096
What's that you're drawing?

158
00:18:21,166 --> 00:18:25,364
It's a man taking Mummy away
on the tray, and here's a tree.

159
00:18:30,876 --> 00:18:34,972
Dada! Guess what?
Grandpa let me sit on the tractor.

160
00:18:35,047 --> 00:18:36,036
Hey.

161
00:18:39,184 --> 00:18:40,879
You want to go
and get your things together?

162
00:18:40,986 --> 00:18:43,386
- Why?
- I thought we'd go away for a while,

163
00:18:43,522 --> 00:18:44,989
...just you and me.
- Where?

164
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:47,319
I don't know, a road trip.

165
00:18:47,392 --> 00:18:49,553
- What will we do?
- What do you want to do?

166
00:18:49,628 --> 00:18:53,587
- Go to Splash Planet.
- We'll see. Go and get your stuff.

167
00:18:58,837 --> 00:19:02,329
- Is this a good idea?
- I obviously think so.

168
00:19:07,346 --> 00:19:09,177
Thanks for taking him.

169
00:19:09,882 --> 00:19:12,646
- Where will you go?
- I don't know yet.

170
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:16,420
Running away is never the answer, Joe.

171
00:19:16,522 --> 00:19:18,956
Look, he sees me as someone
who comes home after weeks away,

172
00:19:19,091 --> 00:19:20,854
bringing presents.

173
00:19:22,227 --> 00:19:24,593
We need to spend some time together.

174
00:19:24,663 --> 00:19:26,631
- And afterwards?
- Afterwards what?

175
00:19:26,732 --> 00:19:29,758
Well, when you need to work,
will you expect me to have him then?

176
00:19:29,835 --> 00:19:32,269
- Not if you don't want to, no.
- No, that's not what I'm saying.

177
00:19:32,371 --> 00:19:36,068
Bea, I left my other boy
when he was six to be with Katy.

178
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:37,972
I need to know how to talk to him.

179
00:19:38,043 --> 00:19:40,068
I need to know how to comfort him
if he needs it.

180
00:19:40,145 --> 00:19:41,874
Look, this isn't about a week
on the road, Joe.

181
00:19:41,947 --> 00:19:45,212
I mean, this is not about sweets
and treats and God knows what else.

182
00:19:45,317 --> 00:19:49,014
This is about structure and routine
and security.

183
00:19:49,121 --> 00:19:51,180
I'm his father. It's my decision.

184
00:19:51,990 --> 00:19:55,949
- I think you're making a big mistake.
- Wouldn't be the first time.

185
00:19:58,797 --> 00:20:00,492
Give Nana a kiss.

186
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:04,127
- Bye, Nana.
- Bye-bye, darling.

187
00:20:05,771 --> 00:20:06,795
Bye.

188
00:20:16,081 --> 00:20:19,915
<i>All the wild horses</i>

189
00:20:25,157 --> 00:20:29,093
<i>All the wild horses</i>

190
00:20:34,166 --> 00:20:39,570
<i>Tethered with tears in their eyes</i>

191
00:20:45,010 --> 00:20:50,505
<i>May no man's touch ever tame</i>

192
00:20:52,951 --> 00:20:58,116
<i>May no man's reigns ever chain you</i>

193
00:21:00,158 --> 00:21:02,718
<i>And may no man's weight...</i>

194
00:21:02,794 --> 00:21:04,386
Can we get a car like that?

195
00:21:04,463 --> 00:21:06,761
- A convertible?
- One without a roof.

196
00:21:06,832 --> 00:21:08,231
Why?

197
00:21:08,333 --> 00:21:11,996
So Mummy can see me in the car
and drop down messages to me.

198
00:21:15,173 --> 00:21:16,435
Can we?

199
00:21:31,023 --> 00:21:35,323
Hey. What are you doing? Stop it.

200
00:21:37,029 --> 00:21:38,894
Artie. Stop it.

201
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:44,631
Artie. Stop it!

202
00:21:48,473 --> 00:21:52,375
What is it? What's the matter?
Are you hungry? Do you want a drink?

203
00:21:53,278 --> 00:21:55,371
Talk to me, sweetheart. What is it?

204
00:22:04,923 --> 00:22:06,914
We'll go to the shop, okay?

205
00:22:07,025 --> 00:22:09,858
We'll go to the shop
and I'll get you a juice and some crisps.

206
00:22:09,928 --> 00:22:12,396
Yeah? Does that sound good?

207
00:22:14,566 --> 00:22:16,966
Are you going to come in
and help me choose?

208
00:22:26,712 --> 00:22:29,044
I don't want orange juice.

209
00:22:29,114 --> 00:22:30,604
What are you talking about?
You always have orange.

210
00:22:30,682 --> 00:22:33,014
I said
I don't want orange juice.

211
00:22:34,119 --> 00:22:38,954
Artie... Artie, it's all right.
Look, there's crisps, okay?

212
00:22:39,024 --> 00:22:40,855
You're hungry. Just eat some crisps.

213
00:22:43,795 --> 00:22:45,729
Oh, for God's sake.

214
00:22:54,639 --> 00:22:56,197
What can you do?

215
00:22:57,042 --> 00:23:01,570
Pick him up. He's upset. Comfort him.

216
00:23:01,646 --> 00:23:03,807
- Give him a cuddle.
- He doesn't want me to.

217
00:23:03,882 --> 00:23:05,611
- Rubbish.
- Well, it's like he's having a fit.

218
00:23:05,684 --> 00:23:08,084
You don't cuddle people
when they're having a fit, do you?

219
00:23:08,085 --> 00:23:10,352
- You're vile.
- True.

220
00:23:12,190 --> 00:23:15,057
I couldn't leave him like that.
Talk to him.

221
00:23:15,127 --> 00:23:18,221
The trouble is, it's not me he wants.
It's you.

222
00:23:36,481 --> 00:23:38,312
I'm sorry, sweetheart.

223
00:23:39,751 --> 00:23:41,343
That's all right.

224
00:23:58,403 --> 00:23:59,961
What are you up to in there?

225
00:24:02,307 --> 00:24:03,638
Artie?

226
00:24:09,069 --> 00:24:11,106
Can I do it again, Daddy?

227
00:24:11,107 --> 00:24:14,418
- Oh, my God.
- Can I, Daddy? Can I?

228
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:17,984
Please, can I? Can I?

229
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:21,990
Yes.

230
00:24:23,328 --> 00:24:25,023
Here goes!

231
00:24:26,431 --> 00:24:27,728
Again! Again!

232
00:24:27,799 --> 00:24:30,324
Hang on. Hang on.
You need some more water.

233
00:24:32,671 --> 00:24:34,434
Big splash coming up!

234
00:24:52,090 --> 00:24:53,250
Artie?

235
00:25:03,268 --> 00:25:04,860
Sweetheart...

236
00:25:51,283 --> 00:25:53,615
I'm the king of the rock!

237
00:26:04,963 --> 00:26:07,124
Welcome back, travelers.

238
00:26:08,567 --> 00:26:09,727
I think it's a chocolate...

239
00:26:09,801 --> 00:26:12,861
- Here you go, mate.
- Thanks.

240
00:26:12,971 --> 00:26:14,438
What's the second number?

241
00:26:14,506 --> 00:26:17,373
Eat up, Daniel. Come on.

