01:21:12,234 --> 01:21:15,431
- Sorry?
- There is no boyfriend.

948
01:22:10,992 --> 01:22:16,123
Artie. Can you see which one's me?

949
01:22:17,666 --> 01:22:20,931
- The one with the football, that's me.
- No, it isn't.

950
01:22:21,303 --> 01:22:23,066
- Yes, it is.
- No, it's not.

951
01:22:24,039 --> 01:22:27,975
Mr. Warr? I've spoken to Harry.

952
01:22:29,511 --> 01:22:31,103
I'm really sorry.

953
01:22:32,047 --> 01:22:35,642
This is really rather awkward.
He doesn't want to see you.

954
01:22:38,720 --> 01:22:40,779
- I see.
- He has games.

955
01:22:42,824 --> 01:22:44,416
- Right.
- We can certainly talk.

956
01:22:44,526 --> 01:22:48,121
- I have a few minutes.
- Not just at the minute, thank you.

957
01:22:49,798 --> 01:22:50,856
Sweetheart?

958
01:23:06,281 --> 01:23:08,545
Where are you going? Artie.

959
01:23:08,917 --> 01:23:11,886
Harry! Harry!

960
01:23:11,987 --> 01:23:14,046
- Artie, come back.
- Harry! Harry!

961
01:23:15,690 --> 01:23:19,717
Harry! Harry! Harry!

962
01:23:24,032 --> 01:23:26,432
- What are you doing here?
- We've come to see you.

963
01:23:26,501 --> 01:23:28,332
We want you to be with us again.

964
01:23:28,403 --> 01:23:30,871
- Look, I'm really sorry.
- I don't want to see you.

965
01:23:30,939 --> 01:23:32,099
Harry.

966
01:23:48,089 --> 01:23:49,681
Come on.

967
01:24:04,305 --> 01:24:05,465
Hi, lads.
What are you having?

968
01:24:05,540 --> 01:24:06,871
Coke and a squash, please.

969
01:24:06,941 --> 01:24:08,238
Did you boys see Jones' tackle,
then?

970
01:24:08,309 --> 01:24:09,901
Yeah. He didn't get up
for a while.

971
01:24:09,978 --> 01:24:12,310
- What do you expect?
- Same as always, thanks.

972
01:24:12,680 --> 01:24:15,547
I wasn't going to take on the fullback.
He looked like 30.

973
01:24:15,683 --> 01:24:17,947
You can't tell the difference
between him and their coach.

974
01:24:18,086 --> 01:24:19,485
I'll get these.

975
01:24:22,223 --> 01:24:24,157
We used to come in here
after games, too.

976
01:24:24,225 --> 01:24:25,988
That's 5.50, please.

977
01:24:28,163 --> 01:24:29,960
- Can we talk?
- Thanks.

978
01:24:30,999 --> 01:24:32,864
I'll see you in a sec.

979
01:24:36,004 --> 01:24:38,302
- Where's Artie?
- He's just there.

980
01:24:45,680 --> 01:24:47,705
I'm really sorry about what happened.

981
01:24:47,782 --> 01:24:51,115
I should never have left you guys alone.
It was wrong.

982
01:24:52,720 --> 01:24:55,280
And I'm sorry
that you didn't enjoy Australia more.

983
01:24:55,390 --> 01:24:57,085
I loved Australia.

984
01:24:58,993 --> 01:25:02,190
Well, that it wasn't everything
you wanted it to be.

985
01:25:04,199 --> 01:25:06,963
I need to ask you something

986
01:25:07,035 --> 01:25:10,971
...and I want you to listen to me.
- Of course.

987
01:25:11,506 --> 01:25:13,599
I mean, really listen to me.

988
01:25:13,675 --> 01:25:15,506
- I do.
- No, you don't.

989
01:25:17,745 --> 01:25:20,009
Okay, well, I'm listening now.

990
01:25:21,349 --> 01:25:23,283
Why did you leave me?

991
01:25:25,120 --> 01:25:28,180
- When you went with Katy.
- You know why.

992
01:25:32,127 --> 01:25:34,595
I fell in love with someone else.
She was pregnant.

993
01:25:34,662 --> 01:25:37,028
No. Why did you leave me?

994
01:25:38,299 --> 01:25:41,962
I mean,
why didn't you take me with you?

995
01:25:42,203 --> 01:25:46,003
I wanted you to take me with you.
I wanted to be with you.

996
01:25:47,242 --> 01:25:50,700
I can honestly say
the thought never crossed my mind.

997
01:25:52,981 --> 01:25:57,975
You were so young, I thought
a child should be with his mother.

998
01:25:58,119 --> 01:26:00,314
- Didn't you miss me?
- God, yeah.

999
01:26:03,424 --> 01:26:05,085
But, you know,
there was this new baby.

1000
01:26:05,086 --> 01:26:08,121
- I was trying to get it right.
- So you just left me with her.

1001
01:26:08,122 --> 01:26:10,123
- With your mother.
- With my mother who hates me.

1002
01:26:10,198 --> 01:26:11,995
Don't be ridiculous.
Your mother adores you.

1003
01:26:12,066 --> 01:26:14,193
See? You don't listen.

1004
01:26:14,769 --> 01:26:18,261
I try and tell you how I feel
and you say I'm ridiculous.

1005
01:26:20,074 --> 01:26:21,268
I'm sorry.

1006
01:26:27,849 --> 01:26:30,374
- I had no idea.
- How could you?

1007
01:26:30,985 --> 01:26:34,284
You were playing happy families
on the other side of the world.

1008
01:26:37,825 --> 01:26:40,726
- You never wanted me.
- No. That's not true.

1009
01:26:46,067 --> 01:26:50,003
- I'm sorry you feel like this.
- Yeah, well, deal with it.

1010
01:27:05,753 --> 01:27:09,086
- Harry's bear.
- We'll give it to him another time.

1011
01:27:09,190 --> 01:27:11,215
No, he's with his friends.
You'll embarrass him.

1012
01:27:11,359 --> 01:27:13,589
But I want to give it to him!

1013
01:27:50,498 --> 01:27:54,025
Daddy, there's a car here
without a roof.

1014
01:27:57,405 --> 01:28:00,636
A convertible, like the one we need.

1015
01:28:01,409 --> 01:28:04,537
I must have been
awful to live with sometimes.

1016
01:28:04,646 --> 01:28:09,606
Daddy, I'm trying to read,
but I can't do all the words.

1017
01:28:10,118 --> 01:28:14,111
Katy? Don't abandon us now.

1018
01:28:15,123 --> 01:28:19,287
Daddy, I'm begging you.
I'm begging you with all my mouth.

1019
01:28:20,161 --> 01:28:21,890
Coming, sweetheart.

1020
01:28:26,167 --> 01:28:27,998
Where's that car?

1021
01:28:41,983 --> 01:28:43,314
Hi.

1022
01:28:46,187 --> 01:28:47,848
What are you doing here?

1023
01:28:47,955 --> 01:28:51,322
- We've been to see Harry.
- Yeah? How was that?

1024
01:28:52,026 --> 01:28:55,018
- Not too good.
- I'm not surprised.

1025
01:28:56,030 --> 01:28:58,624
- Why do you do things like this?
- Things like what?

1026
01:28:58,700 --> 01:29:00,429
Well, who just turns up at the door?

1027
01:29:00,501 --> 01:29:04,062
- Have you got a baby in your tummy?
- Yes, I have.

1028
01:29:05,340 --> 01:29:08,867
- My mummy's dead.
- I know.

1029
01:29:10,144 --> 01:29:13,477
- Congratulations.
- Harry didn't tell you?

1030
01:29:14,148 --> 01:29:15,410
Not a word.

1031
01:29:18,920 --> 01:29:20,444
Would you like
something to drink, Arthur?

1032
01:29:20,555 --> 01:29:22,079
What have you got?

1033
01:29:22,080 --> 01:29:23,422
Why don't you come in
and we'll have a look?

1034
01:29:23,524 --> 01:29:26,721
- Don't you have a lesson?
- Just come in, for God's sake.

1035
01:29:26,794 --> 01:29:29,092
- Is Jason home?
- Just come in.

1036
01:29:46,114 --> 01:29:48,105
Thanks for seeing me.

1037
01:29:49,317 --> 01:29:51,046
You want some tea?

1038
01:29:56,290 --> 01:30:00,954
- God, I hated this school.
- Really? I never knew.

1039
01:30:02,130 --> 01:30:05,827
- Your name's on every board.
- It was awful here then.

1040
01:30:06,367 --> 01:30:09,063
- It's pretty awful here now.
- Really?

1041
01:30:13,007 --> 01:30:17,103
So, your mum's pregnant?
You didn't tell me.

1042
01:30:18,045 --> 01:30:21,139
- It's going to be a girl.
- That's nice.

1043
01:30:21,983 --> 01:30:24,952
It'll be cool to have a sister, won't it?

1044
01:30:30,057 --> 01:30:32,890
So, where do you fit in, do you think?

1045
01:30:35,196 --> 01:30:36,993
I'm not sure I do.

1046
01:30:40,601 --> 01:30:45,402
Okay, look, I'm going to take
Artie back to Australia,

1047
01:30:48,075 --> 01:30:53,308
but what we want, both of us,
is for you to come with us.

1048
01:30:57,018 --> 01:30:59,077
Come and live with us.

1049
01:31:01,989 --> 01:31:04,082
I saw your mum yesterday.
We had a long talk,

1050
01:31:04,158 --> 01:31:06,490
and she wants what's best for you.
She really does.

1051
01:31:06,594 --> 01:31:11,031
So, if you did want to come,
she will support that.

1052
01:31:12,500 --> 01:31:16,027
Artie and I have talked about it a lot,
and it's definitely what we want.

1053
01:31:17,004 --> 01:31:19,029
He just adores you.

1054
01:31:22,877 --> 01:31:27,211
Obviously, it's a huge decision, so
you don't have to decide this second.

1055
01:31:27,648 --> 01:31:29,707
I didn't feel safe there.

1056
01:31:31,085 --> 01:31:35,078
- What, the 10 most poisonous snakes?
- No, Dad. You.

1057
01:31:37,158 --> 01:31:38,921
You scared me.

1058
01:31:41,329 --> 01:31:43,263
That won't happen again.

1059
01:31:46,000 --> 01:31:50,767
Whatever you decide, I promise, I'll be
a better father to you from now on.

1060
01:31:56,077 --> 01:31:58,068
I can't, Dad...

1061
01:31:59,981 --> 01:32:01,312
I can't.

1062
01:32:03,618 --> 01:32:05,085
All my friends are here.

1063
01:32:09,390 --> 01:32:11,221
It's not fair on Mum.

1064
01:32:17,164 --> 01:32:18,358
I'm sorry.

1065
01:32:30,511 --> 01:32:33,742
- So, when are we going?
- Tomorrow morning.

1066
01:32:34,348 --> 01:32:38,284
When is Harry coming? Daddy?

1067
01:32:38,719 --> 01:32:43,122
He's not coming with us, sweetheart.
He's going to stay here.

1068
01:32:43,958 --> 01:32:46,290
He'll come for holidays and stuff.

1069
01:32:50,598 --> 01:32:52,122
It's your fault!

1070
01:33:35,042 --> 01:33:38,910
<i>Please do not leave
your luggage unattended at the station.</i>

1071
01:33:38,980 --> 01:33:42,074
<i>Luggage left unattended
may be removed without warning</i>

1072
01:33:42,149 --> 01:33:45,175
<i>or destroyed or damaged
by the security services.</i>

1073
01:33:45,319 --> 01:33:46,843
Artie.

1074
01:33:56,797 --> 01:33:58,025
Artie?

1075
01:34:03,804 --> 01:34:05,465
- Artie?
- Daddy!

1076
01:34:19,754 --> 01:34:22,279
Don't you ever check your messages?

1077
01:34:23,391 --> 01:34:24,915
We don't have much time.

1078
01:34:43,077 --> 01:34:45,136
You won't lose him. I promise.

1079
01:34:45,246 --> 01:34:49,080
The saving on school fees alone is
like five trips back here a year.

1080
01:34:49,150 --> 01:34:50,981
Thank you for saying that.

1081
01:34:51,519 --> 01:34:54,181
Good luck with the baby.
Keep us posted.

1082
01:35:28,322 --> 01:35:32,122
<i>So, here we are,
a father and two sons,</i>

1083
01:35:32,123 --> 01:35:34,893
<i>surviving in a household
without women.</i>

1084
01:35:36,464 --> 01:35:39,024
<i>Like a year-long experiment
in a satellite,</i>

1085
01:35:39,100 --> 01:35:41,398
<i>free from earthly influences.</i>

1086
01:35:46,540 --> 01:35:49,805
Harry, did you just wipe your face
with a dog?

1087
01:35:50,778 --> 01:35:53,338
Hey, wipe your face with your own dog!

1088
01:35:56,317 --> 01:36:00,344
<i>See the pyramids along the Nile</i>

1089
01:36:01,989 --> 01:36:03,354
<i>Watch the sunrise on a tropic isle</i>

1090
01:36:03,424 --> 01:36:06,882
<i>Given its inadequacies
as a child-rearing unit,</i>

1091
01:36:08,362 --> 01:36:11,126
<i>I like it.</i>

1092
01:36:11,565 --> 01:36:15,968
<i>It's Home Alone,
except there's three of us.</i>

1093
01:36:22,743 --> 01:36:23,937
- Gosh!
- Yes!

1094
01:36:24,044 --> 01:36:25,705
- I'm off.
- Take that, chuckles.

1095
01:36:25,780 --> 01:36:27,077
- I'll be back by 6:00.
- Out!

1096
01:36:27,148 --> 01:36:28,809
- No, it was in. It was in.
- Out.

1097
01:36:28,883 --> 01:36:30,851
- Referee?
- Six-five to Artie.

1098
01:36:30,918 --> 01:36:34,684
- Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!
- Bye, then.

1099
01:36:35,122 --> 01:36:36,316
Bye, Daddy.

1100
01:36:36,557 --> 01:36:39,754
<i>You belong to me</i>

1101
01:36:40,995 --> 01:36:44,954
<i>I'd be so alone without you</i>

1102
01:36:46,500 --> 01:36:50,994
<i>Maybe you'll be lonesome too...</i>

1103
01:36:52,673 --> 01:36:55,164
Come on.
Come on, Vegemite. Liquorice.

1104
01:37:00,648 --> 01:37:03,481
<i>I don't think
he brushes his teeth enough.</i>

1105
01:37:03,584 --> 01:37:05,745
I agree with you about that.

1106
01:37:06,287 --> 01:37:08,983
<i>Can't you get him to do it twice a day?</i>

1107
01:37:09,123 --> 01:37:11,557
Once a week would be an advance.

1108
01:37:11,659 --> 01:37:14,992
I can't understand
why they're so white, though.

1109
01:37:16,430 --> 01:37:19,365
Is he brushing them in secret,
do you think?

1110
01:37:21,402 --> 01:37:24,963
What about his hair?
When did he last wash his hair?

1111
01:37:25,039 --> 01:37:29,100
Well, they wash it when he gets it cut.
And I'm rigid about that.

1112
01:37:29,844 --> 01:37:33,336
He gets it cut twice a year,
whether he needs it or not.

1113
01:37:39,153 --> 01:37:43,055
- He seems happy.
- I'd say he is, usually.

1114
01:37:46,527 --> 01:37:48,222
God, he misses you.

1115
01:37:51,198 --> 01:37:54,395
- He still remembers me?
- Of course.

1116
01:37:55,970 --> 01:37:58,803
Don't ever think that we'll forget you.

1117
01:38:00,274 --> 01:38:02,504
You'll always be his mother.

1118
01:38:05,713 --> 01:38:08,147
- One more thing.
- What's that?

1119
01:38:08,249 --> 01:38:10,444
Will you do
one more thing for me, Joe?

1120
01:38:10,551 --> 01:38:11,882
Anything.

1121
01:38:12,820 --> 01:38:14,754
Buy that convertible.

1122
01:38:19,860 --> 01:38:20,986
I will.

1123
01:38:22,329 --> 01:38:24,524
And if anyone asks, I'll tell them why.

